Logical Operators

When we need to test for 2 or more conditions we use Logical Operators

    AND OR NOT
    &&  ||  !


boolean cold=true;
boolean rain=true;


AND

true && true -> TRUE
true && false -> FALSE
false && true -> FALSE
false && false -> FALSE


OR

true || true -> TRUE
true || false -> TRUE
false || true -> TRUE
false || false -> FALSE



if (cold, rain) {
        sout ("I will stay at home");
}


NOT - reverse the condition

       boolean boo=!false;
       sout(boo); // true


Switch Statement -

syntax

switch (variable) {

case value1:
        code A;
        break;
case value2:
        code B;
        break;
default:
        Code C;
        break;
}